and their <HI>Sences,</HI> &amp;c. <HI>Ars. potenter.</HI><NOTE N="1" PLACE="foot"><HI>Erase</HI> "Ars. potenter." R. W. Ms. Ann.</NOTE></P>
<P>2. <HI>The</HI> Devourers of the Poor and helpless, <HI>po|tenter,</HI><NOTE N="2" PLACE="foot">Erase "potenter."<HI>R. W. Ms. Ann.</HI></NOTE>
<HI>&amp;c.</HI></P>
<P>3. The <HI>proud</HI> puft up with <HI>foolish Confidences,</HI> bold|ly
Crying, <HI>Lord open to us, for we,</HI> &amp;c. also the Con|trary
to these three I might inlarge on, <HI>and not
Impertinently, but let him that readeth understand,</HI> is
in<NOTE N="3" PLACE="foot">Change "is in" to "y^n." <HI>R. W. Ms. Ann.</HI></NOTE> <HI>pag.</HI> 64. where<NOTE N="4" PLACE="foot">Erase "where." <HI>R. W. Ms. Ann.</HI></NOTE> G. <HI>Fox</HI> brings in <HI>Ieremiah Ives</HI>
