their Heart or Tongues said, or Hands hid, <HI>&amp;c.</HI></P>
<P>4. It is notoriously contrary to what G. <HI>Fox,</HI> and
his so often [39] Clamour that the <HI>Kingdome of God
consists in,</HI> or its Nature is in <HI>Righteousness, and Peace
and Ioy in the holy Spirit:</HI> as opposite to the King|dome
in the <HI>Pharisees,</HI> and all <HI>Hipocrites</HI> and <HI>pro|phane,</HI> &amp;c. as Hell to Heaven.</P>
<P>5. The thing is so notoriously childish and ri|diculous,<NOTE PLACE="marg">The grace of God is offered to all, but em|braced by few that are freely chosen</NOTE>
<HI>&amp;c.</HI> that a King should affirm he was an
