<P>7. Yea,<NOTE PLACE="marg">G Fox a most visi|ble and idle prater of Invisi|bilities.</NOTE> G. <HI>Fox</HI> and his <HI>Foxians,</HI> for all their be|ing
in God, and some of their proud and silly Ans|werings
in Courts, that they live in God, and dwell
in God, yet they disowne not their own <HI>visible
Congregatings</HI> and <HI>Assemblings,</HI> their <HI>visible Teachers,
Overseers,</HI> or <HI>Bishops,</HI> their <HI>visible</HI> and <HI>audible per|formances</HI>
and <HI>Worships, praying, preaching, singing,</HI>
&amp;c. and w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">y then doth this [43] poor notoriously
<HI>visible Cheatour</HI> thus prate of <HI>Invisibilities especially
in times of peace and not in</HI> Elias <HI>Case?</HI></P>
<P><HI>The</HI> 22 Instance <HI>is in</HI> pag 84. <HI>where G.</HI> Fox <HI>brings
in his opposite</HI> Magnus Byne; <HI>saying,</HI> [The Scriptures
