<P>3. What kind of Grace it is that so easily per|sons
Fall away away from, and part withal.</P>
<P>2. As to <HI>Ezek.</HI> 18. How doth it follow, that be|cause
the word Righteousness in which <HI>Fox</HI> in his
<HI>wonted Burrough,</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">The Word Righteous|ness of many sig|nifications</NOTE> signifies divers things, that there|fore
in this first place it must signify the Imputed
